    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> do you have any idea why does it happen? It's <code>rust-out-of-tree-module</code> and I do everything as was described in quick-start<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/V3r0T70CClbbk25b9L8W69UW/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/V3r0T70CClbbk25b9L8W69UW/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-dimensions=\"1202x1218\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/35136/V3r0T70CClbbk25b9L8W69UW/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>root@ubuntu2404arm:~/rust-for-linux#<span class=\"w\"> </span>make<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>rustavailable\nRust<span class=\"w\"> </span>is<span class=\"w\"> </span>available!\nroot@ubuntu2404arm:~/rust-for-linux#<span class=\"w\"> </span>uname<span class=\"w\"> </span>-r\n<span class=\"m\">6</span>.9.0-rc1+\nroot@ubuntu2404arm:~/rust-for-linux#\n</code></pre></div>",
