    {
        "content": "<ul>\n<li>are you importing the <code>GFP_KERNEL</code> constant?</li>\n<li>which version of the kernel are you using?<br>\n  depending on that you might need to change <code>push</code> to <code>try_push</code>.</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 464024893,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1724240246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Last time we talked here I understood we talked about kernel v6.9. The <a href=\"http://rust_minimal.rs\">rust_minimal.rs</a> from kernel v6.9 has</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">numbers</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">try_push</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">72</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">numbers</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">try_push</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">108</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">numbers</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">try_push</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">200</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"740136\">@Nikolai Shv</span> Please check if you took <a href=\"http://rust_minimal.rs\">rust_minimal.rs</a> sample code from recent kernel with your v6.9 kernel version?</p>",
        "id": 464026215,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1724240534
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah so v6.9 probably doesn't have the allocator flags stuff yet</p>",
        "id": 464026875,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1724240657
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See commit 9872947486bb (\"rust_out_of_tree: use the new allocation APIs\"):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Diff\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span>   rust_out_of_tree: use the new allocation APIs\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>   Required since Linux's commit 5ab560ce12ed (\"rust: alloc: update `VecExt`\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>   to take allocation flags\") [1].\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>   Link: https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240328013603.206764-1-wedsonaf@gmail.com/ [1]\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>   Signed-off-by: Miguel Ojeda &lt;ojeda@kernel.org&gt;\n<span class=\"gs\">---</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>rust_out_of_tree.rs | 6 +++---\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n\n<span class=\"gh\">diff --git a/rust_out_of_tree.rs b/rust_out_of_tree.rs</span>\n<span class=\"gh\">index ce8c706329eb..1f829a4619a6 100644</span>\n<span class=\"gd\">--- a/rust_out_of_tree.rs</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+++ b/rust_out_of_tree.rs</span>\n<span class=\"gu\">@@ -21,9 +21,9 @@ impl kernel::Module for RustOutOfTree {</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>        pr_info!(\"Rust out-of-tree sample (init)\\n\");\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>        let mut numbers = Vec::new();\n<span class=\"gd\">-        numbers.try_push(72)?;</span>\n<span class=\"gd\">-        numbers.try_push(108)?;</span>\n<span class=\"gd\">-        numbers.try_push(200)?;</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+        numbers.push(72, GFP_KERNEL)?;</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+        numbers.push(108, GFP_KERNEL)?;</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+        numbers.push(200, GFP_KERNEL)?;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>        Ok(RustOutOfTree { numbers })\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>    }\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 464026927,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1724240680
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"740136\">@Nikolai Shv</span> You can simply go back one commit and it should work for you.</p>\n<p>Having said that, if you want to do Linux kernel development, it is recommended that you use mainline, i.e. Linus' tree (the latest <code>-rc</code> typically), rather than older versions. Then you can use the latest template.</p>",
        "id": 464027201,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1724240784
    }
]